 legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ."   \par \par \uc2 Japan Sumitomo Corporation chairman Kenji Miyahara said another area that had to be tackled by the government was the rampant corruption that contributed to the high cost of doing business in the country.   \par \par \uc2 "Indonesia will remain uncompetitive compared to other countries unless it manages to reduce the rampant corruption," he said.   \par \par \uc2 During the key investment forum, held to attract about US$120 billion worth of investment to develop the country's infrastructure over the next five years, the government promised it would move swiftly to fix the weak investment climate here and provide various incentives for investors through what it called a "new partnership".   \par \par \uc2 In what may be part of the efforts to ease investor concerns, the government signed the Jakarta Declaration with representatives of companies from 20 participating countries in the summit. The declaration underscores the government's commitment to remove all bureaucratic hurdles to private sector investment.   \par \par \uc2 The government promised to finalize all of the required policies to improve the investment climate, as well as revising any problematic regulations, within six-months. It also pledged to honor all contracts made with the private sector.   \par \par \uc2 "We have to make this work otherwise that's it, we will never be able to do this again," said Vice President Jusuf Kalla at the summit's closing ceremony, underlining the government's commitment to the infrastructure projects.   \par \par \uc2 Attended by more than 500 companies from 20 countries around the world, the government offered some 91 projects valued at US$22.5 billion during the summit. A second batch of projects valued at about $57.5 billion will be offered during a summit in November.   \par \par \uc2 "Under the new government, legal certainty is here and will remain," said Minister of Justice and Human Rights Hamid Awaluddin.   \par \par \uc2 "I am aware that my country's bureaucrats need to be improved and the regulations should be made more investor friendly," said Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Aburizal Bakrie, adding that a number of investors from several countries had expressed interest in investing here.   \par \par \uc2 But Deutsche Bank director for Singapore Paul Sempere said that despite the assurances, there remained questions about whether the government could realize its promises.   \par \par \uc2 "The intention is always good at the top, but to translate these intentions into reality in the bureaucracy is another question," he said.   \par \par \uc2 He said investors would wait until the government was able to fulfill its commitments on private investment.   \par \par \uc2 "I think the way forward is to use some pilot projects ... a maximum of two or three pilot projects in each of these sectors, and push that," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Jakarta Declaration <p> * Indonesia's Vision for Infrastructure Development<br>   \par \par \uc2 - Government will focus on non-commercially viable projects<br>   \par \par \uc2 _ Government will focus on sectoral reforms to ensure<br>   \par \par \uc2 sustainable private sector participation<br>   \par \par \uc2 - Government will enact program to support greater private sector involvement in infrastructure<br> <p> * Removing Bureaucratic Hurdles for Private Investment<br>   \par \par \uc2 - All contractual commitments will be honored<br>   \par \par \uc2 - Develop clearly articulated strategies and sectoral plans<br>   \par \par \uc2 - Invite investors to participate in upcoming fast-track infrastructure investments<br>   \par \par \uc2 - Issue an interim \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  that addresses the issue of private participation in infrastructure development<br>   \par \par \uc2 - Issue a \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  that will s