\par\par \b \uc2 Government decides to adopt 'enclave' FTZ in Batam   \b0\par\par\uc2 Zakki P. Hakim, The Jakarta Post/Jakarta   \par \uc2 568 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 January 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The government finally decided to maintain the previous government's proposal for an "enclave" free trade zone on the industrial island of Batam, despite potential opposition within the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Aburizal Bakrie told reporters on Monday that the government decided to limit the free trade areas to certain places on the island despite the House's desire to make the whole island a free trade zone.   \par \par \uc2 However, the minister believes the House will accept the enclave approach.   \par \par \uc2 "There will be no conflict at the House," Aburizal stated on the sidelines of the CNBC Strategic Forum entitled "The New Indonesia 2005: \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Action".   \par \par \uc2 Aburizal said this government's plan was slightly different from the previous one proposed by the Megawati administration.   \par \par \uc2 The government will free manufacturers within the designated industrial zones from paying import duties, while those outside the zones can enjoy the same facility through bonded warehouses.   \par \par \uc2 He said the government was still making assessments before making a decision on whether neighboring Rempang and Galang islands would be able to be complete free trade zones (FTZ).   \par \par \uc2 During the forum, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono said in his keynote speech that the government had a very good working relationship with the House.   \par \par \uc2 "Vice President Jusuf Kalla's success in being elected leader of Golkar, the largest party in the House, will significantly add more stability to my government," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Since Kalla took over the reins of Golkar in December, there has been no real opposition in the house as the party has 128 of 550 seats at the House, in addition to the administration's support from several medium-sized parties.   \par \par \uc2 The previous government under Megawati Soekarnoputri and the previous House failed to reach an agreement on the status of Batam as an FTZ.   \par \par \uc2 Last September, the House endorsed its bill that granted FTZ status to the whole of Batam Island. The bill was opposed by the government.   \par \par \uc2 Without the government's approval, the law cannot take effect, creating further \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  for investors on the island, which, since 1978 has been promoted by the government as an industrial bonded zone to attract foreign investors.   \par \par \uc2 Batam has become one of the most attractive manufacturing and industrial locations in Southeast Asia, playing host to some 600 foreign companies and absorbing over US$3 billion in foreign investment.   \par \par \uc2 The government has argued that extending full FTZ status to the whole island would cause envy from other regional administrations that do not have FTZ status.   \par \par \uc2 As soon as Susilo was sworn in this past October, the Singapore government, which is just a 45-minute ferry ride from Batam, expressed hope that the new government would quickly decide on the FTZ status of Batam. Otherwise, existing and potential investors would turn away to competing investment areas in China and Vietnam.   \par \par \uc2 Singapore Foreign Minister George Yeo said Batam had the potential to become a leading industrial center like China's Shenzhen within 10 years, but only if the lingering legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  was quickly resolved.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) chairman MS Hidayat said the decision to turn all of Batam into an FTZ area or to adopt the enclave FTZ was not an issue for investors. It was more important that the status of Batam be clearly defined, he added.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050125e11p0000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
