iting professionals to sit on the new board of directors for national flag carrier Garuda Indonesia.  \par \par \uc2 Garuda management has been in limbo for more than a year following the failure of the previous government to appoint a replacement board due to alleged collusion in the selection process.  \par \par \uc2 Susilo himself earlier this week urged executives of state enterprises not to provide facilities for people claiming to be members of his family or other key state officials, saying that "such a practice is at the root of corruption and must be stopped."  \par \par \uc2 Despite the absence of the necessary \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Sugiharto was optimistic that it would not discourage him from working to improve the performance of state enterprises.  \par \par \uc2 In his early days in power, Sugiharto had planned to replace most of the incumbent key officials at his office, following allegations from the business community and legislators that the officials were involved in corrupt practices.  \par \par \uc2 The changes are not critical because three of the state minister's six deputies have resigned due to illness and retirement. The posts have remained empty until now.  \par \par \uc2 A high-ranking official at the state minister's office, who requested anonymity, said many officials were reluctant to work as their futures were shrouded with \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  following the delay in the reshuffle program.  \par \par \uc2 "The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  has concerned the officials. They are always wondering whether they are going to be replaced or not. Pak Sugiharto must immediately make up his mind and appoint new officials to end the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said.  \par \par \uc2 However, Sugiharto said the management reshuffle at state firms could only be done if his own office had already appointed new people into the new structure.  \