\par\par \b \uc2 Preparing  \highlight22\uc2 public \highlight\uc2  for higher fuel prices   \b0\par\par\uc2 Vincent Lingga , Jakarta   \par \uc2 815 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 February 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 While \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  rationale was initially the main demand arising from the plan to increase fuel prices, discussion is now focused on how to make the painful measure politically acceptable to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  and palatable to the general \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Virtually no one will argue against the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  necessity to cut the huge fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , most (80 percent) of which have been enjoyed by people of the middle- and high-income brackets.   \par \par \uc2 Fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which could explode to over Rp 70 trillion (US$7.8 billion) this year, also cut into the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for poverty alleviation and other social safety net programs, and threaten \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability.   \par \par \uc2 Even more damaging is that \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  encourage gross inefficiency in fuel use -- while the country has now become a net oil importer -- hinder the development of alternative energy and make export smuggling a highly lucrative business.   \par \par \uc2 However, as the government experienced in early 2003, what had been established as economically rational and approved through a national political consensus at the House was not automatically accepted by the general \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The government in late January, 2003 was forced to scale back the fuel price hikes it introduced early that month due to a massive wave of demonstrations, thereby damaging its policymaking credibility.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  acceptance, which is the key to the effectiveness of the upcoming fuel-price increase to achieve its objectives, will depend on whether the reform can be promoted as fair.   \par \par \uc2 Therefore, the bold move to slash fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is expected before the end of next month, cannot be conducted as a single, isolated measure. It must be introduced in a package with other programs to ensure fairness in sharing the burden and to build a conducive environment for rational \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  opinion. .   \par \par \uc2 And the price increase should not be so steep as to unduly shock the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 This is what the government has been preparing for the last few weeks, though the process has been rather slow and haphazard.   \par \par \uc2 The government is trying to establish fairness through the protection of the poor from bearing the brunt of the higher prices. The government has said it will maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  for kerosene, the most widely used fuel in poor households.   \par \par \uc2 A Cabinet meeting last week decided to increase budgetary appropriations for helping poor families bear the higher prices to almost Rp 18 trillion from Rp 7.3 trillion originally allocated. These funds will be used for health services, education, rice \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , rural infrastructure and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  housing.   \par \par \uc2 But \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  acceptance also depends on the government's willingness to take on its full share of the burden through minimizing waste and inefficiency caused by corruption and by truly behaving and acting out of a real sense of urgency and crisis.   \par \par \uc2 The government should go all out to convince the people that the fuel-price hike is really for their benefit, otherwise a new bout of social unrest could surface at the expense of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political stability.   \par \par \uc2 The government needs to establish a reliable mechanism for ensuring that the poor are fully protected from the additional burdens to be inflicted by the new fuel-pricing \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- that is, that the remaining \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  reach their target beneficiaries.   \par \par \uc2 Encouraging, though, is that the government already has a fairly comprehensive map of the country's poverty pockets so that the various forms of assistance have a better chance of reaching their target beneficiaries.   \par \par \uc2 However, the government and business leaders are yet to sit down and calculate the impact of the higher fuel prices on production costs for goods and services, and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  needs to design appropriate monetary policies to manage anticipated inflationary pressures.   \par \par \uc2 These preparations are all necessary to prevent a reaction of panic. At a time when many people are still suffering the brunt of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis and millions of others are either unemployed or underemployed, additional burdens stemming from higher fuel prices could easily incite \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  anger.   \par \par \uc2 The absence of justice and an equitable sharing of burdens could sabotage the whole reform movement.   \par \par \uc2 Massive street demonstrations, such as those in early 2003, would only make things murkier, increase \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and affect political stability. This in turn could press down the rupiah exchange rate and consequently further increase fuel prices and foreign debt servicing at the expense of government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on social safety net programs.   \par \par \uc2 Moreover, it would be almost impossible to do business under a wildly fluctuating exchange rate.   \par \par \uc2 There are only a few weeks left for the government to consult the House about the planned fuel-price hike, prepare the business community to cope with its consequences and sell the idea to the general \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Time is not on the government's side. Delaying the measure would only create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , breed speculation and further damage the government's policymaking credibility.   \par \par \uc2 The writer is a senior editor of The Jakarta Post.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050224e12o00006\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
