22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  resources ranging from agriculture, manufacturing, and oil and mining, had the potential to grow by 5.5 percent as projected by the government.   \par \par \uc2 Good \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management and declining debt, were the reasons S&P gave in December when it raised Indonesia's long-term foreign currency credit rating one step to a B+ from a B and upgraded the country's long-term rupiah debt rating two levels to BB from a B+.   \par \par \uc2 Both ratings were credited with a positive outlook.   \par \par \uc2 An S&P "BB" rating means that a country is less vulnerable yet still faces \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  from adverse business and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions in its capacity to meet financial commitments.   \par \par \uc2 While the two ratings are respectively five and four levels below a more dependable "A" investment grade, an improved rating nevertheless reduces a country's investment risks, allowing its government to borrow funds at cheaper rates.   \par \par \uc2 Ogawa said one of the main obstacles that could frustrate the government from accomplishing its programs was the existing ineffective and inefficient bureaucracy.   \par \par \uc2 Another issue was the recent increase of inflation in the country, which required the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  quickly apply foreign currency policies.   \par \par \uc2 "The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's policies are very important, as well as how investors interpret the policies," he said. "If BI is too slow with its policies, it might affect the country's macroeconomic foundation."   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has said it would act more aggressively to control the volatility of the rupiah and the inflation through its interest rate instrument, which Ogawa said was sensible \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Commenting on the government's decision to delay its bond offerings for this month, Ogawa said that it would unlikely affect Indonesia's rating outlook, as this was mostly caused by the market's current situation.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050401e1410001b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
