, Amanah cited a recent decision by the Constitutional Court to annul the Electricity Law as having created more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the future direction of Indonesia's reforms.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, on decentralization, Amanah said that there should be better coordination to avoid the issuance of conflicting regulations by local administrations, which would only result in a high-cost \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "The decentralization \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  should in fact produce benefits, not problems for the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she said, adding that continued confusion over decentralization would do no good for the government's efforts to lure investment.   \par \par \uc2 "Investment in infrastructure, for instance, would result in a more efficient \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she said.   \par \par \uc2 "A low-cost \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would bring the prices of goods, and thus inflation, down," she said.   \par \par \uc2 Last but not least, the government must increase its efforts to create jobs for the more than 2 million people entering the nation's workforce every year, and increase development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on poverty reduction schemes.   \par \par \uc2 Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Outlook<BR>   \par \par \uc2 2004 2005 2006 2007 <BR> GDP 5.1 5.5 6.0 6.5 <BR> GDI/GDP 21.3 22.3 24.2 26.1<BR> Inflation rate 6.2 5.9 5.5 5.5<BR> Export growth 9.4 6.0 7.0 8.0<BR> \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  1.3 0.8 1.0 0.5<BR>   \par \par \uc2 Source: Asian Development Bank   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050407e14700017\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
