\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Tax \highlight\uc2  reform could set off virtuous  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  circle   \b0\par\par\uc2 David E. Sumual , Jakarta   \par \uc2 954 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 April 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Amid the barrage of negative news concerning Indonesia's financial markets lately, there has been an encouraging development in that the government finally launched its long-awaited US$1 billion international bond issue last week. This new issuance should effectively boost the supply of foreign exchange and help Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to reach its targeted \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 0.8 percent of GDP in 2005.   \par \par \uc2 Yet for the time being, the jitters in the markets remain with investors still concerned over inflationary pressures. Thus, the prospects of higher-than-expected inflation in the near term and the likelihood of further hikes in \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory note (SBI) rates seem to outweigh the successful global bonds issue. Also disheartening is the weakening rupiah, which has been, in part, influenced by the United States Federal Reserve's commitment to further hikes in its benchmark rate, the stubbornly high world oil prices and the declining inflows in the country's current account.   \par \par \uc2 Given a lack of fresh domestic leads, the outlook for the rupiah may remain bleak so long as the decline in inflows in the current account surplus cannot be offset by stronger capital inflows. This expectation is also confirmed by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's projection that the country may endure a shortage in foreign exchange of about $600 million in the private sector this year.   \par \par \uc2 Nevertheless, there is actually a development that could mark a turning point in the rupiah's fortunes. It is the government's intention to speed up the submission of the new \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  for deliberation. This could be a potent catalyst to greater optimism on the prospects for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 A complicated \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  system is one of investors' main concerns in doing business in Indonesia. Many 'loopholes' in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regulations make it possible for unscrupulous \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials and taxpayers to collaborate. Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  system also combines the function of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration under one agency, creating a powerful \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  office.   \par \par \uc2 In other words, the system that now exists effectively makes the Directorate General of \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  an entity that determines its own receipt targets and policies, meaning less effective administration and independent policies. Other crucial problems, such as the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , uncompetitive \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates and low numbers of individual taxpayers, are some issues that need to be addressed in the proposed \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws.   \par \par \uc2 Another politically related issue that may draw the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 's attention would be the drafting of the bill on a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty. This could become particularly controversial as managing the whole process of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform is far from simple, given the inherently political nature of an such 'big-bang' \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs.   \par \par \uc2 Although the law may finally be endorsed by the House, the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  process of deliberating upon a comprehensive \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  program, especially the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty law, could be tricky and take longer than expected. As a crucial arena for debating the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform issues, the legislature could thus block, or alter significantly, any \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform proposal.   \par \par \uc2 Moreover, the House is now in recess until May. And given its urgency, the House may first discuss the 2005 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision. So, the amended \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws not even be discussed until the third quarter of this year at the earliest.   \par \par \uc2 Besides widening the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  base in future years, the primary benefit of introducing a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty actually rests on the belief that billions of dollars that reportedly left the country following the financial crisis in 1997 would be lured back. Of course, not all of the $40 billion to 60 billion in funds that were reportedly transferred abroad during the crisis could be expected to flow back into the country following the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Nobody knows how much exactly would be brought in; and some of the overseas assets may be illiquid. However, if the government's claim that the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty could rake in at least $6 billion is true, those capital inflows would likely strengthen the rupiah.   \par \par \uc2 It should be noted that $6 billion is not petty cash and it is clearly enough to have some impact on the domestic currency market. The positive impact on the rupiah could even be substantial considering the psychological announcement effect of the passage of a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty law on the domestic players who have long dollar positions.   \par \par \uc2 Although a bit different in terms of its \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  exemption mechanism, the effect of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform on the rupiah could be similar to the effect of the American Jobs Creation Act on the dollar bulls lately.   \par \par \uc2 The law that was signed by Bush in late October 2004 gives \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  cuts for foreign subsidiaries of U.S companies in repatriating their profit earned overseas. By awarding those companies a one-year repatriation opportunity with a significant discount in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate, around $135 billion could reportedly be brought back in one year. This expectation along with the Fed's strong signal that it will further hike its benchmark rate may be the reason for both momentum trading and short covering rallies in the dollar recently.   \par \par \uc2 In contrast to a developed country like the U.S however, many things remain to be done in fixing Indonesia's business environment.   \par \par \uc2 Other than \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform, there are still many laws and regulations that can create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a high cost \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , thus hampering the investment-driven \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If the lawmakers and the government could expedite the bureaucratic process in amending those laws and regulations, there is a good chance that foreign capital would stream in, providing support for the rupiah.   \par \par \uc2 The writer is an Analyst of Danareksa Research Institute. This article is strictly a personal view.   \par \par \