s and the 2001 terrorist attacks on New York and the Pentagon.   \par \par \uc2 Based on a report from the Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM), the United States came ninth on the list of the biggest investors in Indonesia in 2004 and in the first five months of this year.   \par \par \uc2 The American Chamber of Commerce in Indonesia (AmCham), a lobby group which represents over 300 U.S. companies in Indonesia, has said that the high level of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  risk and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  have reduced the appetite of foreign investors to come here.   \par \par \uc2 The risks and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  include problems such as corruption, \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  inconsistency, weak law enforcement, and poor coordination among government departments, as well as between central, provincial and local governments.   \par \par \uc2 "From an investor's point of view, major concerns in Indonesia are transparency and the quality of regulations, the control of corruption, the rule of law and regulatory certainty, as well as overall government effectiveness," AmCham president Joe C. Bartlett said in a presentation last year.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050714e17e00017\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
