\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Budget \highlight\uc2  gives wrong signals  \b0\par\par\uc2 799 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 August 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 The financial market has reason to be uneasy about the 2006 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono unveiled to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Tuesday.  \par \par \uc2 It seems the key assumptions used for revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates deviate far from what most market players expected.  \par \par \uc2 While most analysts anticipate that oil prices will fluctuate at a range of US$55-60/barrel within the foreseeable future, as against the actual average of $50.50 in the first seven months of this year, the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumes an average price of $40 for the whole of next year.  \par \par \uc2 It is completely unreasonable to expect such a steep fall in oil prices from the current assumption of more than $63 within the next four months to bring them down to an average $40 next year even though, as the government supposes, the world demand for oil will decline and supplies from OPEC will increase.  \par \par \uc2 The government seems unwilling to learn from its current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  debacle, which was caused by its gross mistakes in underestimating the oil price cycle.  \par \par \uc2 As the government stubbornly deluded itself into believing that the era of cheap oil would soon return, it initially predicted for the 2005 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  that oil prices would average $24 for the whole of the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. But the government was forced to revise the price estimate to $35 in March. This was the price used as the basis for setting the 29 percent increase in domestic fuel prices in that month. But the estimate was again revised in June to $45 before the government finally accepted, in its latest estimate for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , that the average price for this year would hover at least at $50.60.  \par \par \uc2 The government also seems overly optimistic of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth for next year, as if denying that the skyrocketing oil prices are likely to damage growth prospects and affect macroeconomic stability.  \par \par \uc2 While the International Monetary Fund has predicted a decline in the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth to 4.3 percent this year from 5.1 percent last year, and the Central Statistics Agency announced on Monday that the rate of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth fell from 6.2 percent -- year-on-year basis -- in the first quarter to 5.54 percent in the second quarter, the government still expects a robust growth of 6.2 percent next year.  \par \par \uc2 As the country is already a net oil importer with a daily import need of around 350,000 barrels, grossly underestimating the oil price average could result in misguided \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies and threaten macroeconomic stability as fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would reach unsustainable levels, thereby causing inflation to spiral and pushing down the rupiah and forcing \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to skyrocket.  \par \par \uc2 Higher-than-estimated oil prices would also severely hurt the country's balance of payments, cut into foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  and consequently trigger stronger speculative attacks on the rupiah. To defend the rupiah, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would have to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and this credit crunch would choke the business sector.  \par \par \uc2 Likewise, the overly optimistic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth estimate could upset the targets of a 26.4 percent increase in income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts and 27.5 percent rise in value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and luxury sales \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues set for next year, which together are responsible for about 61 percent of total domestic revenues.  \par \par \uc2 This potential vicious circle should be among the apprehensions of market players in reading the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal, and this negative perception is quite worrisome because a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan is supposed to communicate the right signals about bureaucratic behavior, prices, priorities, intentions and commitments.  \par \par \uc2 Further down the road, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused by the unrealistic \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates would prompt most investors to further wait on the sidelines and this in turn could abort the target of a 15.2 percent expansion in investment set for next year.  \par \par \uc2 It would have been much better, in terms of \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  adjustments, if the government was more conservative in regard to an oil price estimate, gearing up for the worst situation with oil prices foreseen above $50. After all, it would be much easier to reallocate a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  surplus in case oil prices turned out lower than the estimate, rather than having to take painful measures to cover a bigger \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in case oil prices are much higher.  \par \par \uc2 Predictability is important for the efficient and effective implementation of policies and programs because the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector will perform better where there is stability in macro and strategic \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the funding of the prevailing \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . However, this draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is instead causing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 It is, therefore, imperative for the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the government to revise the key assumptions for the draft 2006 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and consequently estimates for revenues and \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  closer to market realities.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050819e18j0000g\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
