\par\par \b \uc2 Govt completes draft  \highlight22\uc2 tax \highlight\uc2  laws   \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 483 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 August 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Realizing that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regime has long discouraged investors, the government is moving to improve the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws by addressing taxpayers' concerns over \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in collection and rebates.   \par \par \uc2 The Ministry of Finance's Directorate General of \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  has completed the revision of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws, the third major \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform, which includes Law No. 16/2000 on general \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  arrangements and procedures.   \par \par \uc2 I Made Gde Erata, head of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law revision team, said the biggest breakthrough in the draft revision was the introduction of a time limit for \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  procedures and a selective audits of taxpayers. The establishment of a special commission to supervise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials and gather complaints from taxpayers, was also important, he said.   \par \par \uc2 "What the business community really wants to see is more on \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administrative reform to improve certainty in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law enforcement by providing time limits for any \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  procedures," Erata told The Jakarta Post recently.   \par \par \uc2 He said the draft laws, which were part of the government's key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform measures, were primarily aimed at attracting foreign investments in order to drive higher \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.   \par \par \uc2 According to the draft law on general \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  arrangements made available to the Post , taxpayers categorized by the directorate as "good" corporate or private citizens should be able to claim refunds for income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  within three months, and for value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) in just one month without needing any audits to clarify the amounts.   \par \par \uc2 For other taxpayers, the period for claiming refunds would remain the same -- 12 months.   \par \par \uc2 Deciding who would go into the category of "good" taxpayers will be determined later by the ministry.   \par \par \uc2 The draft law also stipulates that if the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate fails to issue the claimed refunds within the given period, it must pay 2 percent interest a month on the unpaid funds.   \par \par \uc2 The directorate will also be required to acknowledge any objections from taxpayers if it fails to settle their claims by the deadline and sanction officials who fail to complete their jobs on time.   \par \par \uc2 At present, taxpayers remain at the mercy of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  auditors when trying to claim rebates as there is no prescribed time limit, encouraging taxpayers to bribe the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials to get refunds sooner.   \par \par \uc2 However, under the draft law, taxpayers can file a complaint to the Ministry of Finance's Inspectorate General if they are extorted by the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials and report to it any corruption within the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office.   \par \par \uc2 The directorate has also finished drafting the revision to Law No. 17/2000 on income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law No. 18/2000 on VAT on goods and services and luxury sales \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The revision package was submitted to President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono on Tuesday by the State Secretary, with the government scheduled to submit it to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  for deliberation next month.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050822e18m00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
