\par\par \b \uc2 BI ups rate to defend rupiah   \b0\par\par\uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has once again moved in to help the beleaguered rupiah -- while at the same time trying to ward off a looming inflation hike -- as it raised its interest rate to a double-digit level.   \par \uc2 297 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 September 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) governor Burhanuddin Abdullah announced on Tuesday the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has increased its benchmark BI Rate again by 50 basis points -- or half a percent -- to 10 percent, following a 75-point hike to 9.5 percent last week as part of its monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  package to help bolster the rupiah.   \par \par \uc2 The rate hike was also aimed at helping dampen inflation, which BI said could rise to 9 percent by the end of the year, ahead of the government's plan to hike domestic fuel prices again, and the ongoing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of global oil prices.   \par \par \uc2 "Inflationary pressures will rise if the fuel price hike happens," he said.   \par \par \uc2 The government is forecasting 8 percent inflation and a 6 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth this year.   \par \par \uc2 To further limit the rupiah's volatility, BI will also tighten local forex trading, by prohibiting banks from margin trading the rupiah against all other currencies, as well as conducting market intervention through one- to seven-day swap transaction instruments as of Sept. 15.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, starting on Oct. 1, BI will also require banks to better maintain their net open position -- the difference between foreign currency assets and liabilities -- and offer three- to six-month swap facilities for hedging purposes.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah has come under pressure as soaring oil prices have pushed the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to the brink of a \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  instability, shaking investor confidence in the currency.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah closed at Rp 10,360 a dollar on Tuesday, down 0.4 percent from its finish the previous day. -- JP   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050907e19700001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
