\par\par \b \uc2 Legal certainty focus of  \highlight22\uc2 tax \highlight\uc2  draft   \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 511 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 September 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 In a bid to protect long-term investments, the government is placing emphasis on legal certainty for the business community, rather than \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives, in its draft revision on the regional \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and user charges law.   \par \par \uc2 Minister of Finance Jusuf Anwar said the revision was mainly aimed at providing a legal instrument to annul locally issued bylaws that could hurt investment.   \par \par \uc2 "We are concerned by several bylaws issued by local administrations as they have discouraged local and foreign investors. The revision is primarily aimed at preventing unfavorable bylaws from taking effect," he said recently.   \par \par \uc2 Following the endorsement of the Autonomy Law in 2001, most administrations in provincial, regental and municipal levels have used their newly gained power as a shortcut to raise local \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the expense of the long-term good of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Surveys revealed that during the initial year of the decentralization program, many businesses suddenly found themselves mired in legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the regional administrations claimed additional \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and levies.   \par \par \uc2 The problem has prompted the government to revise the regional \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and user charges law.   \par \par \uc2 On the other hand, the draft law contains fewer incentives for businesses -- with several policies on \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates likely to hurt certain industries, such as tourism and manufacturing.   \par \par \uc2 The draft revision stipulates that local administrations can collect entertainment \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  from bars, discotheques, night clubs, karaoke bars, massage parlors, fashion shows and beauty pageants to a maximum of 75 percent -- from the current 35 percent -- of the organizers' revenue.   \par \par \uc2 Cultural performances and arts exhibitions will also be \b \highlight22\uc2 taxed\b0 \highlight\uc2  to a maximum of 35 percent.   \par \par \uc2 The draft law will also allow regency/municipal administrations to collect "environmental" \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  from manufacturing companies to a maximum of 0.5 percent of production costs.   \par \par \uc2 Jusuf said although there were new \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates, objects and subjects proposed in the draft law, regional administrations could not collect them immediately, since all bylaws on local \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and retribution should be approved by the government.   \par \par \uc2 "It is clear in the draft law that when imposing a new bylaw on \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 , local administrations should take into account taxpayers' financial capability. The government will ensure that the \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  will not be detrimental to the people," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Under the revised law, the government has the right to delay or reduce the disbursement of "\b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  balance funds", should the regional administration refuse to revoke its controversial bylaw. \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  balance funds are funds allocated to regional administrations that are set aside from the annual state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The lack of a legal instrument and clear sanctions have made local administrations refuse to comply with the government's requests to annul their more controversial bylaws.   \par \par \uc2 The revision to the law -- the third since 1997 -- stipulates that a local administration will be required to submit their bylaws within seven days to the Ministry of Home Affairs and the Ministry of Finance for review and approval.   \par \par \uc2 The draft law is being formulated by the Ministry of Finance's \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Financial and International Collaborative Studies Agency (BAPEKI).   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050912e19c00013\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
