\par\par \b \uc2 Activists  \highlight22\uc2 uncertain \highlight\uc2  over role of KKR   \b0\par\par\uc2 Ridwan Max Sijabat , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 554 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 September 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 4\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Skepticism prevails among human rights activists over the capability of the Truth and Reconciliation Commission (KKR) in handling unresolved rights abuse cases because the law dealing with it is considered far from workable.   \par \par \uc2 Speaking in an international conference on the Truth and Reconciliation Commission in Indonesia, they demanded that Law No. 27/2004 on the commission be reviewed through consultation with the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The event, jointly organized by Friedrich Ebert Stiftung, Elsam, New Zealand's International Aid and Development Agency and The Jakarta Post , also featured speakers from South Africa, Guatemala, Peru and Argentina -- four African and Latin American countries where such a commission has been proven capable.   \par \par \uc2 The President is still selecting 21 candidates from 42 names proposed by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  to sit on the commission.   \par \par \uc2 Ifdhal Kasim, director of the Institute for \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Research and Advocacy (Elsam), said the commission would be unable to seek a comprehensive solution to the unresolved past human rights abuse cases because the law says the commission can only investigate individual cases and limits its authorities.   \par \par \uc2 "The commission is tasked only to seek an alternative (out of court) dispute settlement. If the government is committed to national reconciliation, the commission should be given the full authority to uncover the truth behind unresolved human rights abuse cases and to understand what happened in a broader historical, socio-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and sociopolitical context.   \par \par \uc2 "The commission should not only determine the kinds of violations, victims and perpetrators but also provide an objective context for the abuses so that the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including the victims, knows who should be held accountable," he said.   \par \par \uc2 The commission has the right to investigate a case but has no authority to use force against those who fail to appear when it summons them for questioning or to testify in a hearing.   \par \par \uc2 Almost all military and police officers who stood trial at the human rights court for East Timor, Tanjung Priok and Abepura atrocities were acquitted.   \par \par \uc2 Enny Suprapto, a member of the National Commission on Human Rights (Komnas HAM), said the nation would lose the momentum to investigate the cases since the commission's mandate would end in seven years.   \par \par \uc2 "The momentum for reconciliation is there as we are now moving toward a full-fledged democracy. When the commission ends its mandate, most people will have forgotten past human rights abuses and will no longer see the urgency of resolving the cases," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Rev. Baskoro, lecturer at Sanata Dharma University in Yogyakarta, said that to be fair, the past human rights abuses should be viewed in a broader national and international historical context.   \par \par \uc2 "Human rights violations in the past involved the military as the government's agent to create social, political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conflicts. The mass killing of communist supporters in 1965 must also be linked to the Cold War between the former Soviet Union and the United States, which were competing for support for their ideologies and their \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  interests in Asia," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Eduardo Gonzales, member of the Truth Commission in Peru, suggested that the government propose changes to the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  to make it workable.   \par \par \uc2 "Another alternative is for Elsam, along with other non-governmental organizations, to bring the law to the Constitutional Court for a judicial review," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020050913e19d0000a\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Inflation Rate May Reach 12 Percent  \b0\par\par\uc2 268 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 October 2005\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 Bisnis Indonesia  \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: State Minister/Head of the National Development Planning Board Sri Mulyani Indrawati revealed there was a possibility the inflation rate might increase to 12%. In the meantime, September's year-on-year inflation rate reaches 9.06 percent, the highest in the past 33 months.  \par \par \uc2 "Expectation for the inflation rate has soared... the inflation rate can increase by 3 percent from 9 percent to 12 percent," she said after the launching of the Savings Guarantor Institution in Jakarta, yesterday  \par \par \uc2 However, Sri Mulyani added that the post-fuel prices hike inflation rate would depend on responses made by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI).  \par \par \uc2 In the meantime, IMF representatives in Indonesia was reviewing Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook following \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused by the second fuel prices hike, avian influenza virus, and Bali bombing, which could increase the inflation rate by the yearend.  \par \par \uc2 "We are still evaluating it. General estimation reveals there will be an increase of 3 percent-4 percent in the inflation rate this year," disclosed Stephen Schwartz, IMF Senior Representative in Jakarta.  \par \par \uc2 The Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) in its current report revealed that September's year-on-year inflation rate reached 9.0