\par\par \b \uc2 Externals blamed for bleak showing  \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta  \par \uc2 549 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 October 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono blames external factors for the government's failure to achieve several key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  goals this year, setting aside criticism over the performance of his \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers in bringing improvement to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 The devastating tsunami disaster, higher global oil prices and recent terrorist attacks on the resort island of Bali were all used by Susilo to defend his \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team amid a growing calls for a Cabinet shake-up.  \par \par \uc2 "It has been a very tough first year for my government. There have been several unpredictable incidents that caused several of our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets to become unattainable this year," said Susilo before a delegation of Japanese businessmen grouped under the Japan External Trade Organization (JETRO) on Monday.  \par \par \uc2 Susilo said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team's concentration in improving the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had been disrupted by these external factors.  \par \par \uc2 He believed external factors played a key role in the declining value of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar, as well as the accelerated full-year inflation, which had surpassed the government's initial single-digit estimation.  \par \par \uc2 Susilo's remarks came days before the first year's anniversary of his government that falls on Oct. 20, when he had pledged to make a review of the performance of all his ministers. It is unclear whether Susilo's statements defending his ministers are an indicator that he may not reshuffle the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team.  \par \par \uc2 Under the last revision of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government lowered its target for the rupiah exchange rate from Rp 9,500 to Rp 9,800 to the dollar, despite the fact that the local currency has been hovering at over Rp 10,000 for the past two months.  \par \par \uc2 Some economics ministers have also upped their forecast for full-year inflation from 8.6 percent to about 12 percent this year, with the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth projection dropping from 6 percent to 5.7 percent.  \par \par \uc2 With lower growth, the government's target of reducing unemployment by about three million is likely to be unattainable. As of last year, the country's open unemployment stood at 10.3 million.  \par \par \uc2 All this has led to mounting calls from analysts, academicians, businessmen and legislators for a reshuffle in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team.  \par \par \uc2 Critics argue that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not have been hit as hard as it was by the external factors had the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team, led by Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Aburizal Bakrie, provide concrete and comprehensive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies as a buffer to such problems.  \par \par \uc2 Still, Susilo remained upbeat that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be better in the coming years, citing steady improvement in certain sectors attained by his administration this year, including a rise in exports and investment.  \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, during a meeting with the President, a JETRO delegate conveyed his concern over rampant corruption, weak law enforcement and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the interpretation of law, which had all discouraged foreign investors in doing business in Indonesia.  \par \par \uc2 "We believe that the government is determined to make the business climate better. However, Japanese businesses, particularly small-and-medium ones, are concerned about the rampant corruption," said the businessman.  \par \par \uc2 JETRO is a Japanese government-related organization that works to promote mutual trade and investment between Japan and the rest of the world.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020051018e1ai00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
