\par\par \b \uc2 SHIPPING COMPANIES DISAPPOINTED WITH INSA'S PROPOSED THC   \b0\par\par\uc2 792 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 November 2005\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 Asia Pulse Pty Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.   \par \par \uc2 Jakarta, Nov 17 (ANTARA) - Many Indonesian shipping companies expressed disappointment with the Terminal Handling Charges (THC) proposed by the General Chairman of the Indonesian National Shipowners Association(INSA) to the government, as he was believed to be lacking in his knowledge about the problems, especially the international container business, facing the shipping companies in the current globalization era.   \par \par \uc2 Director of the national shipping company PT Samudera Indonesia Asmari Herry told the press in Jakarta on Thursday that he was disappointed with the move of the INSA general chairman regarded as not very wise in dealing with THC problems, and in serving the interest of the stakeholders, namely the customers, Indonesia's national shipping companies, foreign shipping companies (main line operators) and the relevant associations.   \par \par \uc2 "Actually, THC is a matter of business regulated by the free market mechanism based on joint commercial agreement between the shipping companies and the customers," he said.   \par \par \uc2 As INSA general chairman taking care of the welfare of the national shipping companies, he should provide fair inputs to the Ministry of Transportation and overcome the problem proportionately so that the THC problem would not appear as too serious and complex a problem, and triggered negative and biased news reports, he said.   \par \par \uc2 On the same occasion, Surabaya's INSA chairman Rudy Witjaksono said that he was very disappointed with INSA General Chairman's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and move. He said the INSA general chairman did not think of the negative impact of one-sided pressures on foreign shipping companies.   \par \par \uc2 He said that the INSA general chairman should understand that the foreign parties were open to talks and negotiations and could supply relevant and useful inputs to the Ministry of Transportation to reach a consensus and especially to prevent the current confusion and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "We have to realize that Indonesia still has no adequate container fleet for Indonesia's export and import activities, and that Indonesia was still in need of the services of foreign shipping companies," he pointed out.   \par \par \uc2 Rudy also expressed fear if foreign shipping companies launched a boycott by refusing to call at Indonesian ports, one could only imagine its disastrous effect on the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 It may be recalled that Minister of Transportation Hatta Rajasa in his circulars dated October 28 and 31, 2005 addressed to the president directors of PT Pelabuhan I, II, III and IV, has set the terminal handling charges.   \par \par \uc2 The charge on 20-inch Full Container Load (FCL) had been lowered from 150 US dollars to 95 US dollars, and that of 40-inch FCL from 230 US dollars to 145 US dollars.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile the container handling fee for stevedoring of loaded containers had also been lowered, namely for 20'FCLs lowered from 93 US dollars to 70 US dollars, and for 40' FCLs from 139 US dollars to 105 US dollars. The new rates took effect as of November 1, 2005.   \par \par \uc2 In the meantime, the management of the national shipping company Bumi Laut Group Jaka Singgih believed that the THC problems had been exaggerated without first studying the background of THC.   \par \par \uc2 He expressed the need for a business to business dialogue between the relevant associations to reach agreement, to prevent the government from getting a headache and to prevent a confusion in the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 When asked what would be a reasonable THC, Jaka said it should be set by the market mechanism and in a fair dialogue between the customers and the shipping companies in question, to prevent the prevailing sensation.   \par \par \uc2 "I think that if the foreign and national shipping companies in question hold a consultative meeting, an agreement would be reached without going through protracted arguments and unpleasant situation," he said.   \par \par \uc2 However, INSA general chairman Oentoro Surya pointed out that the lowering of the THC which he has proposed to the INSA central executive board was merely aimed at making Indonesia's export commodities competitive on the international market.   \par \par \uc2 "We must have pity for our businesspeople, fuel oil prices had been raised which had caused problems to our businesses including laying off their employees. Therefore, the lowering of the THC is meant as a compensation for the fuel oil price hike," he said.   \par \par \uc2 He also believed that the THC in Indonesia is the highest in the world, as many illegal charges and levies had been justified and legalized. According to Oentoro, the proposed THC had already been discussed by an interdepartmental team, including the ministry of transportation, chaired by the coordinating minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  affairs.   \par \par \uc2 He said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of lowering the THC had been responded to positively by \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  players, especially shipping companies."If the government is solid enough, I am believe they (foreign shipping companies, ed.) would accept this decision," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020051118e1bh00