ction have really engaged in business, but anticipative steps are required to prevent the issue from stimulating a conflict of interest that can lead to new KKN (corruption, collusion and nepotism) practices, according to the President.  \par \par \uc2 He emphasized the need to determine the rules of the game and draw up a code of ethics that must be obeyed by state officials or government officials who enter this domain, where on the one hand they serve as officials and on the other act as businessmen.  \par \par \uc2 The Head of Government expressed his hope that the Presidential Instruction to be issued will be good for all circles, for those engaging in legal and clean business that abides by the rule as well as those suspected of dealing with wrong business or business that reeks of corruption, collusion and nepotism practices.  \par \par \uc2 The Presidential Instruction is not effective for ministers or other officials who are also businessmen, if they have withdrawn from their business, according to Yudhoyono. If a minister has been free from his/her business or stopped temporarily his/her business activities, he is not subject to the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  stipulated in the Presidential Instruction, he said.  \par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020051119e1bi0000d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
